description:
The Dow plunged 450 points at the open after President Donald Trump surprised investors by threatening to impose higher tariffs on China in a tweet. But at midday, the Dow bounced back from its initial low, and was down some 170 points.
The Dow is still up about 14% this year, but the plunge at one point wiped out the past three weeks of gains.
#Trump #Tariffs #CNN #News
title: Trump's tariff threat causes stock market slide

description:
In the midst of a trade war, China imposed high tariffs on various imports, hitting the lobster industry in Maine hard. CNN's Miguel Marquez reports. 

#CNN #News
title: This fisherman, who likes Trump, has a message for the President
